-- Colombia to swap peso bonds, likely inflation-linked, fixed rate - sources
-- 
-- Fri Sep 26, 2014 05:49PM EDT
-- None



BOGOTA, Sept 26 (Reuters) - Colombia is preparing a swap of local peso-denominated Treasury bonds that will likely include inflation-linked and fixed rate, two sources with knowledge of the operation told Reuters on Friday.    (Reporting by Nelson Bocanegra)  ((helen.murphy@thomsonreuters.com; +571-634-4139; Reuters Messaging: helen.murphy.reuters.net@reuters.com))  Keywords: COLOMBIA BONDS/

